    a. Find its mirror `m`.
    b. We must ensure we process the pair `(c, m)` only once. A good way to do this is to only process the pair if `c` is lexicographically less than or equal to `m`. If `c == m`, it's a self-mirror pair. If `c < m`, it's the canonical representation of the pair.

